### **Comprehensive List of AI and Other Tools for Each Stage of a Systematic Literature Review (SLR)**  

Below is a structured **list of AI-powered and conventional tools** that can be used at **each stage** of a **systematic literature review (SLR)**, including **links to access them**.

---

## **ðŸ“Œ 1. Identifying Research Topic & Formulating Research Questions**  
### **AI-Powered Tools for Idea Generation & Topic Exploration**
| **Tool** | **Description** | **Link** |
|---------|---------------|----------|
| **ChatGPT** | AI-powered brainstorming, topic refinement, and research question generation | [ChatGPT](https://chat.openai.com/) |
| **Elicit AI** | AI research assistant that finds papers and extracts key insights | [Elicit](https://elicit.org/) |
| **Research Rabbit** | Helps find connected research papers & visualize topics | [Research Rabbit](https://www.researchrabbit.ai/) |
| **Connected Papers** | Visual tool for exploring relationships between papers | [Connected Papers](https://www.connectedpapers.com/) |
| **Scite.ai** | AI-powered citation analysis to see how papers are referenced | [Scite](https://scite.ai/) |

---

## **ðŸ“Œ 2. Searching & Retrieving Relevant Literature**  
### **Databases & Search Engines**
| **Tool** | **Description** | **Link** |
|---------|---------------|----------|
| **Google Scholar** | Free academic search engine for articles & books | [Google Scholar](https://scholar.google.com/) |
| **PubMed** | Database for biomedical and life sciences research | [PubMed](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/) |
| **IEEE Xplore** | Engineering and computer science research database | [IEEE Xplore](https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/) |
| **Scopus** | Large database of peer-reviewed research articles | [Scopus](https://www.scopus.com/) |
| **Web of Science** | Interdisciplinary citation index | [Web of Science](https://www.webofscience.com/) |
| **Semantic Scholar** | AI-powered search tool for scholarly articles | [Semantic Scholar](https://www.semanticscholar.org/) |

### **AI-Powered Search Assistants**
| **Tool** | **Description** | **Link** |
|---------|---------------|----------|
| **Consensus AI** | AI-powered tool that finds research papers based on questions | [Consensus](https://consensus.app/) |
| **Scite Assistant** | AI tool that evaluates research credibility | [Scite](https://scite.ai/) |
| **Litmaps** | AI-assisted tool for tracking citations and research relationships | [Litmaps](https://www.litmaps.com/) |

---

## **ðŸ“Œ 3. Screening & Selecting Studies (PRISMA Framework)**
### **Reference & Literature Management Tools**
| **Tool** | **Description** | **Link** |
|---------|---------------|----------|
| **Zotero** | Free reference manager for organizing studies | [Zotero](https://www.zotero.org/) |
| **Mendeley** | Citation management and PDF annotation tool | [Mendeley](https://www.mendeley.com/) |
| **EndNote** | Advanced reference management software | [EndNote](https://endnote.com/) |
| **Rayyan** | AI-powered systematic review tool for collaborative screening | [Rayyan](https://www.rayyan.ai/) |

---

## **ðŸ“Œ 4. Quality Assessment of Selected Studies**  
### **Tools for Assessing Study Quality & Bias**
| **Tool** | **Description** | **Link** |
|---------|---------------|----------|
| **Cochrane Risk of Bias Tool** | Evaluates risk of bias in randomized studies | [Cochrane RoB](https://methods.cochrane.org/bias/resources) |
| **CASP Checklist** | Critical Appraisal Skills Programme for qualitative studies | [CASP Checklists](https://casp-uk.net/casp-tools-checklists/) |
| **AMSTAR** | Evaluates systematic reviews' methodological quality | [AMSTAR](https://amstar.ca/) |
| **Newcastle-Ottawa Scale (NOS)** | Quality assessment tool for cohort/case studies | [NOS Tool](http://www.ohri.ca/programs/clinical_epidemiology/oxford.asp) |

---

## **ðŸ“Œ 5. Data Extraction & Organization**
### **Tools for Extracting & Structuring Data**
| **Tool** | **Description** | **Link** |
|---------|---------------|----------|
| **Excel/Google Sheets** | Organizing extracted study data | [Google Sheets](https://www.google.com/sheets/about/) |
| **NVivo** | AI-powered tool for qualitative data analysis | [NVivo](https://lumivero.com/products/nvivo/) |
| **ATLAS.ti** | Qualitative coding and thematic analysis | [ATLAS.ti](https://atlasti.com/) |
| **RevMan** | Cochrane's systematic review manager | [RevMan](https://revman.cochrane.org/) |

---

## **ðŸ“Œ 6. Data Synthesis & Analysis**
### **AI & Statistical Tools for Synthesis**
| **Tool** | **Description** | **Link** |
|---------|---------------|----------|
| **Voyant Tools** | AI-powered text mining for qualitative analysis | [Voyant Tools](https://voyant-tools.org/) |
| **VOSviewer** | Visualizes bibliometric relationships between studies | [VOSviewer](https://www.vosviewer.com/) |
| **CiteSpace** | Citation network analysis and trends visualization | [CiteSpace](http://cluster.ischool.drexel.edu/~cchen/citespace/) |
| **R (Metafor Package)** | Meta-analysis and statistical review | [Metafor (R)](https://www.metafor-project.org/) |
| **Python (Scikit-learn, Pandas, Matplotlib)** | AI-assisted data processing and trend analysis | [Scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/) |

---

## **ðŸ“Œ 7. Writing & Reporting Findings**
### **AI Writing Assistants & Research Paper Tools**
| **Tool** | **Description** | **Link** |
|---------|---------------|----------|
| **Grammarly** | AI-powered grammar, clarity, and style improvement | [Grammarly](https://www.grammarly.com/) |
| **Hemingway Editor** | Improves readability of research writing | [Hemingway Editor](https://hemingwayapp.com/) |
| **Trinka AI** | AI-based academic writing assistant | [Trinka AI](https://www.trinka.ai/) |
| **QuillBot** | AI-powered paraphrasing and summarization | [QuillBot](https://quillbot.com/) |
| **Typeset.io** | AI-based research formatting & journal compliance | [Typeset](https://www.typeset.io/) |

